      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hello there! I'd be happy to help you draft that rejection email. You know, it's a bit of a relief to finally get to the final round, but sometimes the decision process is just as tricky as a senior dev trying to debug a race condition in a distributed system.\n\nHere is a draft you can use. It's professional, polite, and keeps the door open for the future, just like a well-structured API that handles edge cases gracefully.\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview for the Senior Developer role at [Company Name]. We truly enjoyed getting to know you and your technical expertise.\n\nAfter careful consideration and reviewing all candidates who reached the final round, we have decided to move forward with another applicant whose background aligns slightly more closely with our current immediate needs. This was a difficult decision, as we believe you are a fantastic developer, and we appreciate the time you spent with our team.\n\nWe hope you understand that this decision is not a reflection of your skills, but rather a matter of fit for this specific project at this specific time. We will keep your resume on file and may reach",
